WEBVTT

00:14:28.375 --> 00:14:31.228
But a more careful look
would tell us otherwise.

00:14:31.252 --> 00:14:34.148
Transparency International ranks China

00:14:34.172 --> 00:14:37.914
between 70 and 80 in recent
years among 170 countries,

00:14:37.938 --> 00:14:40.091
and it's been moving up.

00:14:40.115 --> 00:14:42.154
India, the largest democracy in the world,

00:14:42.178 --> 00:14:44.301
94 and dropping.

00:14:44.325 --> 00:14:47.183
For the hundred or so countries
that are ranked below China,

00:14:47.207 --> 00:14:49.772
more than half of them
are electoral democracies.

00:14:49.796 --> 00:14:53.067
So if election is the panacea
for corruption,

00:14:53.091 --> 00:14:56.310
how come these countries can't fix it?

00:14:56.334 --> 00:14:59.904
Now, I'm a venture capitalist.
I make bets.

00:14:59.928 --> 00:15:02.236
It wouldn't be fair
to end this talk without